WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:46.892
Welcome to Grade 4 English, Unit 4: Community and Communication. Welcome to Unit 4! This unit is all about community and communication — the many ways people share news, ideas, and help with one another. You will read about a library service, a young reporter, and how a whole town shares information. You will learn strong new words like service, deliver, knowledge, information, discover, and priority, and you will use them to talk and write about your own community. By the end, you will be ready to share a message clearly, just like Amal does in this unit's story, “The Circular Plan”. In this short lecture, preview the key ideas and prepare for the independent lesson.

2
00:00:46.972 --> 00:01:11.998
By the end of this unit, you will be able to talk about services and communication in your community, using new unit 4 words. you will also describe places and things using there is and there are. you will also state facts about your town using the present simple (“mail carriers deliver letters daily”). Keep these goals in mind as you work.

3
00:01:12.078 --> 00:01:26.981
Your vocabulary work begins with these words: service, deliver, information, thought, discover, knowledge. Listen to each pronunciation in the vocabulary lab, study its meaning in context, and use the word accurately in your own discussion and writing.

4
00:01:27.061 --> 00:01:41.558
The reading sequence includes The Library That Came to Us and Selma the Young Reporter. Read actively. Identify each text's central ideas, notice viewpoint and reliability, and support every inference with relevant evidence from the text.

5
00:01:41.638 --> 00:02:13.143
The first language focus is Countable and Uncountable Nouns. Some nouns we can count one by one — one book, two books, three books. We call these countable nouns. Other nouns we cannot count as separate items — like water, rice, or information. We call these uncountable nouns. Knowing the difference helps you choose the right words, so your sentences make sense. Notice the structure in the model examples, then apply it deliberately in connected sentences and paragraphs.

6
00:02:13.223 --> 00:02:29.340
In speaking, you will complete Speaking 1: Describe a Service in Your Community. Organise your ideas, use evidence and respond clearly to questions. In writing, you will plan, draft, check and revise. Use the success criteria before submitting your work.

7
00:02:29.420 --> 00:02:45.943
You are ready to begin. Start with the vocabulary lab, continue through reading and comprehension, apply the grammar focus, and complete the speaking and writing practices. Use AI English for hints and feedback, and bring your questions to the live sessions.
